On Mon, 28 Oct 2002 Claralw(-at-)aol.com wrote:

>     I have only pulled apart a couple vw motors that had filters on them, and
> the rod bearings looked loads nicer than those with out.  those without
> always had little marks in the bearing surface.
> Dunno how long term oil magnet would change things (w/o filter).  Muir did
> recommend a magnetic drain plug.   Are those sold by our friendly VW parts
> houses?

Problem with magnetic drain plugs is that they extend too far into the
hole and interfere with the bottom of the strainer.  Second problem is
that the area above the drain plug is a stagnent area, flow-wise.  All the
action is above the strainer.



